<TITLE> HC help sought to get fire equipment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 15 (bdnews24.com)A rights group moved the High Court Sunday, seeking to force the government to buy sufficient equipment to fight high-rise building fire and save lives and properties. Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh filed a writ petition in the High Court bench of justices ABM Khairul Haque and Md.Abdul Hai. The petitioners also sought an order that the Fire Service and Civil Defense directorate prepare a list of necessary fire fighting equipment and submit it to the HC. The judges said they will hear the petitioners next Sunday. The petitioners argued that the absence of equipment was the reason why fire fighters failed to control fire at Bashundhara City tower, which houses Bangladesh's largest shopping mall on its lower floors, on Mar 13 and consequently seven people died and property worth hundreds of millions of taka was destroyed. Secretaries to the ministries of home, finance, disaster management and relief, director general and director (Operation and Maintenance) of Fire Service and Civil Defense were made responden
